<TITLE> Faruq seeks Canadian investment in Kaptai dam </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 5 (bdnews24.com)Commerce minister Faruq Khan on Tuesday called for Canadian investment in Kaptai dam. He focused on scopes for investment in the power and gas sector at a seminar titled "Business and Investment: Canada-Bangladesh initiative" in the office of Dhaka Chambers of Commerce and Industries. "Canada could gain from Kaptai investment, which would benefit Bangladesh as well," the minister said. "The government will put no hurdles to doing business. Rather, the problems and business barriers we have with Canada and other countries will be removed. The next parliament session will discuss the legal barriers, if any." Investors need not worry about political situations, all problems will be discussed in the parliament, he added. Faruq added that the government's procurement policy has been made transparent and doing business easier. "Bangladesh has huge human resource skilled with IT. We want to send out 10000 IT experts this year." bdn
